Gravity Theory for Space Stations - FCF Aligned Synopsis
Core Insight: Gravity in space is not a force to replicate but a constraint to mediate through resonance frequency fields. We carve away impossibilities to let unmanifest potential manifest as low-friction, self-tuning gravity pockets.

